	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=10319><span id= >Aelwulf</span></a><br><span id=notbold>32 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.96]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>This is an old debate with Monks, just depends how you want to play.&nbsp;&nbsp;Some say AGI &amp; DEX, others say STR &amp; STA.  Personally I kind of like a combo of all 4.  STR is better for hitting, STA is better for HP &amp; swinging weapons (even light ones get heavy on long fights), swimming, etc.  AGI is better for your Dodge skills &amp; such.  DEX is pretty much just good for weapon procs &amp; combat skill increases.  If you keep your skills maxxed like a good monkey the latter shouldn't be much of an issue, and the former only if you have a proccing weapon. *shrug*<br>It's all personal preference.  If you can use it great, if not sell it to help pay for a Froggie Crown or something.</p>&nbsp;<br>Harik Sarome<br>The Wandering Monk of Xegony<br>Soldiers of Fortune</td></td></tr>
